142.1	Pledge_of_Allegiance	Pledge of Allegiance	The Pledge of Allegiance of the United States is an expression of loyalty to the federal flag and the republic of the United States of America, originally composed by Christian Socialist Francis Bellamy (1855-1931) in 1892 and formally adopted by Congress as the pledge in 1942. The Pledge has been modified four times since its composition, with the most recent change adding the words "under God" in 1954.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a2/PledgeOfAllegiance1899.jpg/220px-PledgeOfAllegiance1899.jpg
